<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 3:17AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog, some dense, expected this morning...
Fog has developed across the area this morning. This fog is
generally south and west of a line from Williamsburg to Mount
Pleasant to Carthage. Some dense fog has developed with
visibilities of a quarter mile or less. Motorists should drive
with extra caution and allow additional travel time. Use low
beams, reduce speed, and allow for plenty of room between you and
other cars. If dense fog becomes more widespread, a dense fog
advisory may be needed.</description>
